\( \frac{2 \alpha}{3}=-\frac{17}{36}+\frac{1}{3}+\alpha^{2} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \frac{2 \alpha}{3}=\alpha^{2}-\frac{5}{36} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \alpha^{2}-\frac{2 \alpha}{3}-\frac{5}{36}=0 \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Delta=b^{2}-4 a c \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( =\frac{4}{9}+\frac{5}{9}=\frac{9}{9}=1 \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \alpha_{1,2}=\frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^{2}-4 a c}}{2 a} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \alpha_{1,2}=\frac{\frac{2}{3} \mathrm{ml}}{2} \Rightarrow \alpha_{1}=-\frac{1}{6}, \alpha_{2}=\frac{5}{6} \)
</div>

