<div class="red bold">Example 5.3:</div>

Find the solution of the coupled 1st order nonlinear equations by converting them to nonlinear integral equation  <span class="l-example">\( \frac{d u}{d x}=v, \frac{d v}{d x}=x^{3}(u+v), u(0)=1, v(0)=\frac{1}{2} \)</span> when \(x=0\).

<br>
<br>
<div class="red bold">Solution 5.3:</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=u(0)+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \Rightarrow u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( f: x \rightarrow y \)
</div>

<b>Zeroth approximation: </b>
<br>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1, \quad v(x)=\frac{1}{2} \)
</div>

<b>First approximation: </b> Put \(u(x)=1, \quad v(x)=\frac{1}{2}\) in the equation.

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x} x^{2}(u+v) d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{1}{2} d x=1+\frac{1}{2} x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x} x^{3}\left(1+\frac{1}{2}\right) d x=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{3}{2} x^{3} d x \Rightarrow v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{8} x^{4} \)
</div>

<b>Second approximation: </b> Put \(1+\frac{x}{2}, v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{8} x^{4}\) in the equation.
<br>
<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x}\left(\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{8} x^{4}\right) d x=1+\frac{x}{2}+\frac{3 x^{5}}{40} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{x^{4}}{4}+\frac{x^{5}}{10}+\frac{x^{4}}{8}+\frac{3 x^{8}}{64}=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3 x^{4}}{8}+\frac{x^{5}}{10}+\frac{3 x^{8}}{64} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\frac{x}{2}+\frac{3 x^{5}}{40}+\ldots \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3 x^{4}}{8}+\frac{x^{5}}{10}+\frac{3 x^{8}}{64}+\ldots \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x} x^{3}\left(1+\frac{x}{2}+\frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{8} x^{4}\right) d x=\frac{1}{2}+\int_{0}^{x}\left(x^{3}+\frac{x^{4}}{2}+\frac{x^{3}}{2}+\frac{3 x^{7}}{8}\right) d x \)
</div>

