<div class="red bold">Example 5.4:</div>

Find the solution of nonlinear 2<sup>nd</sup> order ordinary differential equation <span class="l-example">\( u(x) . u^{\prime \prime}(x)=\left(u^{\prime}(x)\right)^{2} \)</span> with initial conditions \(u(0)=1, u^{\prime}(0)=1\) at \(x=0\) by converting it to the equivalent integral equation.
<br>
<br>
<div class="red bold">Solution 5.4:</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(0)=1 \quad u^{\prime}(0)=1 \quad x=0 \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x) . u^{\prime \prime}(x)=\left(u^{\prime}(x)\right)^{2} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
Let \( u^{\prime}(x)=v \) be
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u . v^{\prime}=v^{2} \Rightarrow v^{\prime}=\frac{v^{2}}{u} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)=v \Rightarrow u(x)-u(0)=\int_{0}^{x} v d x \Rightarrow u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \) <span class="f-num">(1)</span>
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v^{\prime}(x)=\frac{v^{2}}{u} \Rightarrow v(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{v^{2}}{u} d x \)
</div>

<b>Zeroth approximation: </b> \( \mathrm{u}(\mathrm{x})=1 \mathrm{v}(\mathrm{x})=1 \).

<b>First approximation: </b> Put \( u(x)=1 v(x)=1 \) in the equation

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{v^{2}}{u} d x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} d x=1+x \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{v^{2}}{u} d x=1+\int_{0}^{x} d x=1+x \)
</div>

<b>Second approximation: </b> Replace \( u(x)=1+x, v(x)=1+x \) in the equation

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x=1+\int_{0}^{x}(1+x) d x=1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{v^{2}}{u} d x=1+\int_{0}^{x} \frac{(1+x)^{2}}{1+x} d x=1+\int_{0}^{x}(1+x) d x=1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2} \)
</div>

<b>Second approximation: </b> Replace \( u(x)=1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2}, v(x)=1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2} \)

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x} v d x=1+\int_{0}^{x}\left(1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2}\right) d x=1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2 !}+\frac{x^{3}}{3 !} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( v(x)=1+\int_{0}^{x}\left(1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2}\right) d x \Rightarrow 1+x+\frac{x^{2}}{2 !}+\frac{x^{3}}{3 !} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=x+\frac{x^{2}}{2 !}+\frac{x^{3}}{3 !}+\ldots \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=e^{x} \)
</div>

